## Critical prohibitions

- Never use type escape hatches (`any`, `biome-ignore`, `@ts-ignore`, or unscoped `@ts-expect-error`). Prefer explicit types, `unknown` plus type guards, and narrow unsafe spots at boundaries.
- Fix root diagnostics instead of suppressing them unless the suppression is unavoidable and scoped minimally (not part of baseline BetAgent scaffolding).

## Required stack

- TypeScript strict mode spanning backend + frontend packages.
- Backend uses NestJS 11 modules, Apollo GraphQL, Prisma, PostgreSQL, pgvector embeddings, Redis (BullMQ, pub/sub, Nest micro transports).
- Frontend ships Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, Apollo Client, NextAuth bridging Supabase sessions.
- Biome lint/format complements Zod, react-hook-form, date-fns, sonner integrations when applicable.

## Monorepo map

- `apps/web`: Next dashboard; `@repo/ui` keeps shadcn primitives, `@repo/components` exposes shared JSX, `@repo/core` publishes hooks/util/session glue.
- `services/*`: NestJS microservices composing `services/api` (GraphQL CASL/API), `services/ingest` (fixtures plus odds ingestion with Bull workloads), `services/worker` (queues plus LangGraph analysis writers).

## Package boundaries

- Imports stay directional: primitives -> `@repo/ui`, shared composites -> `@repo/components`, infra -> `@repo/core`, documents -> `@repo/graphql`, DB access -> `@repo/prisma-client`, DI contracts live in `@repo/domain`.

## Core engineering rules

- Keep transports thin; encapsulate persistence + workflows inside domain services guarded by validators.
- Incoming DTOs never leak Prisma clauses; integrations always expose timeouts/backoff tiers; downstream jobs cannot undo persisted writes arbitrarily.
- `ValueEngineService` owns deterministic EV+ arithmetic; prompts never hallucinate payouts.

